{
  "texts": [
    "Information Technology has two main types of publications: those that focus on the technical implementation and the methodology more than the actual task, e.g., Li et al. (2021), and those that focus on technology tasks such as assessing password strength (Abdrabou et al., 2021), user experience (UX) evaluation (Moon et al., 2021), adaptive visualizations (Fu and Steichen, 2022), and contributing to fields like affective computing and cognitive modeling (Alghofaili et al., 2019).",
    "Other Domains holds various publications which could not be clearly assigned to only one of the other four domains.",
    "This includes publications related to driving (Lethaus et al., 2013), aviation (Peysakhovich et al., 2022), maritime (Li et al., 2022), marketing and product design (Moacdieh and Sarter, 2017), and linguistics (Reich et al., 2022).",
    "Learning tasks offer a more detailed perspective on the research focus across the 77 publications.",
    "Similar to the research domains, some publications were categorized under multiple learning tasks."
  ]
}